      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unfortunatly we can’t use the new Http2MultiplexHandler(inboundStreamHandler, upgradeStreamHandler) in the way proposed here.\nFor h2c upgrade, the first HTTP/1.1 request is converted into HTTP/2 stream 1 during `upgradeTo()`. That means the HTTP/2 core pipeline (frame codec + multiplexer) and per-stream handler must already be installed at upgrade time. If we postpone multiplex setup until later (after `HTTPServerPipelineSetup.HTTP_2`), the upgrade request can be delivered before the stream pipeline exists, which risks losing the first request or triggering protocol errors.\n\nThe 2-arg constructor applies `upgradeStreamHandler` only to the single upgraded stream, while all subsequent streams get `inboundStreamHandler`. In our case RESTCONF does not need a special pipeline for the upgrade stream, so splitting pipelines like this is unnecessary and easy to misconfigure.\n\nTherefore we’ll stick with the established server-side pattern (as in Netty’s multiplex server upgrade example): install the multiplexer directly inside `Http2ServerUpgradeCodec(...)`, `new Http2ServerUpgradeCodec(http2FrameCodec, new Http2MultiplexHandler(childInit))`, and keep a single per-stream initializer for all streams (including stream 1).",
